Package org.iogp.gigs

Class Test3005

Object
IntegrityTest
Series3000<Conversion>
Test3005
public class Test3005 extends Series3000<Conversion>
Verifies that the software allows correct definition of a user-defined map projection.
Test description
Test method: Create user-defined projection for each of several different map projections.
Test data: GIGS_3005_userProjection.csv.
Tested API: CoordinateOperationFactory#getOperationMethod(String) and
CoordinateOperationFactory.createDefiningConversion(Map, OperationMethod, ParameterValueGroup).
Expected result: The geoscience software should accept the test data. The order in which the projection parameters are entered is not critical, although that given in the test dataset is recommended.

Usage example

in order to specify their factories and run the tests in a JUnit framework, implementers can define a subclass in their own test suite as in the example below: 
public class MyTest extends Test3005 {
    public MyTest() {
        super(new MyCoordinateOperationFactory());
    }
}
Since:
1.0

      Returns:
      the configuration of the test being run.

    • getIdentifiedObject

      public Conversion getIdentifiedObject() throws FactoryException
      Returns the coordinate operation instance to be tested. When this method is invoked for the first time, it creates the coordinate operation to test by invoking the corresponding method from CoordinateOperationFactory with the current properties map in argument. The created object is then cached and returned in all subsequent invocations of this method.
      Specified by:
      getIdentifiedObject in class Series3000<Conversion>
      Returns:
      the geodetic datum instance to test.
      Throws:
      FactoryException - if an error occurred while creating the coordinate operation instance.
